    "content": "**AI & Robotics Snacks** - May 10, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🧾 Reserv made insurance claims look like compute demand\n\nThe least glamorous back office in finance has apparently discovered growth-stage AI theatrics.\n\n- **The round:** Reserv announced a $125 million Series C led by KKR, with Bain Capital Ventures, Flourish Ventures and strategic clients also joining.\n- **The pitch:** the AI-native TPA says it serves nearly 200 insurers, captives, MGAs and brokers, and wants to scale from 500,000 annual complex claims capacity to 30 million within four years.\n- **The signal:** claims handling is being sold as software throughput, not paperwork with a headset.\n\n*Somewhere, a legacy adjuster just learned their workflow is now a platform narrative.*\n\n**Sources:** [Business Wire](https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20260504407536/en/) | [VentureBeat](https://venturebeat.com/business/reserv-announces-125-million-series-c-financing-led-by-kkr-to-accelerate-ai-driven-transformation-of-insurance-claims/)\n\n---\n\n## 🧱 IREN bought Mirantis because GPUs still need adults\n\nAI cloud operators have discovered the shocking final boss of infrastructure: making customers' clusters usable.\n\n- **The deal:** IREN signed a definitive agreement to acquire Mirantis in an all-stock transaction worth about $625 million at signing.\n- **The assets:** Mirantis brings Kubernetes orchestration, cloud infrastructure support, more than 1,500 enterprise customers and NVIDIA AI Cloud Ready Initiative credentials.\n- **The motive:** IREN says Mirantis will strengthen provisioning, monitoring and enterprise operations as its AI Cloud deployments grow.\n\n*Turns out renting GPUs is only step one. Step two is explaining why the cluster is on fire politely.*\n\n**Sources:** [IREN](https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2026/05/05/3287514/0/en/IREN-Announces-Acquisition-of-Mirantis-to-Strengthen-AI-Cloud-Delivery-Capabilities.html) | [The Block](https://www.theblock.co/post/400032/iren-mirantis-625-million-all-stock-deal-round-out-ai-cloud-platform)\n\n---\n\n## ⛪ AI ethics found a clergy calendar invite\n\nSilicon Valley spent years optimizing for disruption and has now reached the please ask a bishop stage.\n\n- **The meeting:** AP reports Anthropic, OpenAI and other AI firms met faith leaders in New York for the first Faith-AI Covenant roundtable.\n- **The organizers:** the Geneva-based Interfaith Alliance for Safer Communities plans more sessions in Beijing, Nairobi and Abu Dhabi.\n- **The context:** Anthropic has leaned hardest into the frame, pointing to Claude's Constitution and its earlier Pentagon dispute over autonomous weapons and domestic mass surveillance.\n\n*Move fast and break things has become move slowly and consult someone with a collar.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/053a44133c64703f83fd50c9ee6124ea)\n\n---\n\n## 🕵️ Experian says the breach report now has agents\n\nCybersecurity needed another acronym-shaped migraine, so naturally the autonomous software arrived holding credentials.\n\n- **The forecast:** Experian's 2026 Data Breach Industry Forecast says AI could overtake human error as the top cause of breaches.\n- **The failure mode:** Experian warns attackers may inject hostile agents into victims' orchestration or governance layers, turning automation into an attack surface.\n- **The fraud side:** its 2026 fraud forecast also flags agentic AI, deepfake job candidates and cyber break-ins as leading threats.\n\n*The incident-response runbook is going to need a chapter called who authorized the bot to do that.*\n\n**Sources:** [Experian](https://www.experian.com/thought-leadership/business/2026-data-breach-industry-forecast-report) | [Insurance Journal](https://www.insurancejournal.com/news/national/2026/01/13/854019.htm)\n"
  }
]
